    "Compact payload for AM_ArKitRemap_v02 weighted synthesis.",
    "Contributors preserve reverse-map weights (no top-1 collapse).",
    "MouthClose is expected to use explicit branch logic because it is missing from arkit52 extraction.",
    "minWeight: contributors with |weight| < threshold are excluded (removes browlaterall 0.031 artifact).",
    "coupledPairs: targets solved jointly via 2x2 least-squares to eliminate cross-contamination.",
    "coupledGroups: small target clusters solved jointly via NxN least-squares (currently BrowInnerUp + BrowOuterUpLeft/Right).",
    "MouthClose clampMax raised from 0.3 to 0.5 (was hitting ceiling on expressive performances).",
    "MouthClose now derives from LipsTowards + lipsPurseWeight * LipsPurse. lipsPurseWeight calibrated to 0.735 using matched ARKit reference (offset 345.4s, ARKit frame 20724 = MHA frame 0).",
    "jawPurseCompensation: unified visual-opening model. factor=0.75 reduces JawOpen when LipsPurse active. funnelGateScale=2.0 reduces compensation when mouthFunnel source curves are high (open/rounded mouth). puckerFactor (default 0.0) available for pucker-aware cap.",
    "forwardConstraintRatio: relaxed to 1.5 (allows MouthClose up to 1.5x adjusted JawOpen). Real ARKit data has mouthClose > jawOpen in 25% of frames; the old strict constraint (ratio=1.0) was capping MouthClose below its correct level.",
    "smoothing: optional temporal post-processing (disabled by default). Enable for noisy MHA captures."
